  "description": "Fifteen-point scale for expressing a personâ€™s level of consciousness, from fully awake to deep unconsciousness, in a number: the so-called EMV score.\r\nThe Glasgow Coma Scale score or EMV (Eye-Motor-Verbal) score is a scale to measure the extent of consciousness, based on eye, verbal and motor responses to specific prescribed sound and pain stimuli.",
